underlying_goal: To brainstorm and implement a new set of paraphrasing strategies for a sandbagging detection system.
friction_detail: The brainstorming pipeline failed repeatedly due to a code bug, an expired API key, and API connectivity issues. Claude had to debug the code, find new API keys, and switch providers to get the task done.
primary_success: Successfully navigating multiple tool failures to complete the brainstorming, and then creating a well-structured configuration file with the new strategies, correctly placing it within the existing project structure and versioning scheme.
brief_summary: The user wanted to brainstorm new paraphrasing prompts. The automated pipeline failed multiple times, requiring Claude to debug the code and work around API issues. After successfully generating ideas, Claude created a new `strategies_v4.yaml` file containing 26 new strategies and placed it correctly in the project.
